  "text": "UcP2, UcP3, and ant2 are overexpressed in Heart but not in liver of aged Rats UCP2 and UCP3 are expressed in most tissues and organs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . UCPs play a role in regulating H 2 O 2 generation (14) and in modifying energy production in aging tissues [CITATION_3] . Western blot and real-time RT-PCR expression analysis demonstrated that UCP2 and UCP3 were scantily expressed in young and old liver but were upregulated in the heart tissues from old rats compared with young rats (Figure 2A and B) .",
